  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>This is probably best broken up into separate issues ("add alt image texts", 
"add aria tags", etc.) perhaps coordinated by a wiki page, so we can see what 
parts of the site have been tested with Wave and also so folks looking to 
address accessibility issues specifically can find them more easily.  I'd love 
to address these things via the OpenHatch sprint on the 11th or some other in 
person or online group effort.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg4309">msg4309 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: sigmavirus24</th>
   <th>Date: 2014-05-04.15:45:52</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre><a href="http://wave.webaim.org/report#/https://openhatch.org/">http://wave.webaim.org/report#/https://openhatch.org/</a>

Wave is a tool used to determine how accessible a website is for those using
screen readers. This report shows that just openhatch.org has about 27 things it
could fix. An added bonus would be adding aria tags appropriately.

I'm happy to help if this is considered desirable.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
